# Agent Rules

## Tool Definition
- Zod input schema required
- Description in natural language (LLM reads this)
- Risk level: low | medium | high | critical
- Timeout in ms (default 30s)
- Idempotency flag
- Required scopes/permissions

## Tool Execution
- Validate input with Zod
- Check user permissions
- Check tenant scope
- Apply rate limit
- Log to tool_calls table
- Return normalized result
- Catch and wrap errors

## Agent Loop
- Max 25 iterations default
- Token budget enforcement
- Cost tracking per task
- Cancellable via AbortSignal
- State persisted to DB after each step

## LLM Provider
- Abstract via LLMProvider interface
- Streaming support
- Retry with exponential backoff
- Fallback provider on failure
- Track tokens and cost

## Planning
- Plan-and-Execute for multi-step tasks
- ReAct for simple tasks
- Plan stored in agent_tasks.plan
- Replan on failure

## Approval
- Required for high/critical risk tools
- Task pauses on approval needed
- User notified via SSE/WS
- Timeout for approval (5 min default)

## Memory Integration
- Retrieve relevant memories at task start
- Inject into system prompt
- Save important interactions after completion
- Respect token budget

## Observability
- Trace every tool call
- Log model, tokens, cost
- Metric: task duration, tool count, success rate
- Replay support: store full prompt + response